<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="489" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/757.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Smith</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-22">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President Oreste and the Haitian Foreign Office jointly request that the
                            Department have the <hi rend="italic">Nashville</hi> go to Fort Liberty
                            with <pb facs="0451" n="335" xml:id="pg_335"/> orders to Pradel,
                            Minister of the Interior and in command there, to return to Port au
                            Prince. The Government is unable to communicate with Pradel, who is cut
                            off and who is urgently needed here as the strongest man to preserve
                            order.* * *</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>